The Minister of Aviation, Senator Hadi Sirika has said that the second runway for the Nnamdi Azikiwe International Airport, Abuja will be ready before the end of his tenure. The minister stated this during the presentation of the Certificate of Occupancy, CoO, for the expansion of the Abuja Airport runway and other aviation facilities within the airport in Abuja. The Certificate of Occupancy was presented to the minister of aviation on Friday by the Minister of FCT, Mohammed Bello. Sirika said the development of Abuja as one of the fastest-growing cities across the world necessitated the move for the expansion of the Abuja airport to build a second runway and establish major aviation facilities.   EFCC signs MoU with INTERPOL; gets direct access to records…     Brand protection firm set to fight brand-counterfeiting     N6.5m up for grab at teachers’ competition   The minister, while disclosing that he approached the FCT minister for the approval of the land, pledged that all structures would be done following the Abuja master plan and in collaboration with the FCT team. He also said apart from the runway, other major facilities will be completed within the remaining time of his tenure. Speaking earlier, the FCT minister said the total number of land allocated for the aviation facilities purposes is about 12,000 hectares of land which has been reserved in the land bank of the city. He urged the minister to ensure proper supervision and also the collaboration between the FCT and the minister of aviation engineers and workers so that all structures and buildings will follow the due process of the Abuja master plan. The FCT minister also pledged to collaborate with the aviation ministry in achieving the aviation road map.